When I set up bumpVersion to update package.json file, it updates every entry with the current "version": "major.minor.patch"

For example, if I have dependencies in package.json with the same version number as "version": "major.minor.patch", bumpVersion will update all.

For example (package.json):

**"version": "v1.0.0",**
"dependencies": {
    **"xyz": "^1.0.0",**
}

then running bumpVersion patch will make the file appear:
**"version": "v1.0.1",**
"dependencies": {
    **"xyz": "^1.0.1",**
}


It is not desirable to see the other dependencies getting changed.

Jsonpickle.dumps produces a string like this:
`{"py/object": "plumbum.path.local.LocalPath", "py/state": {"_path": "/data/holder/for_mark"}, "py/newargs": {"py/tuple": ["/data/holder/for_mark"]}}}` To unpickle the object there needs to be a way to set the _path property of LocalPath otherwise a set attribute error is thrown.

```
    @property
    def _path(self):
        return str(self)
    #Needed to allow jsonpickle to unpickle the object
    @_path.setter
    def _path(self, value):
        return None

    def _get_info(self):
        return self._path
    def __getstate__(self):
        return {"_path" : self._path}
```

